Here is the complete picture of everything related to `.newsfeed-header` and the feed header/tab system across the codebase.

---

## 1. `.newsfeed-header` CSS Rules

### `client/src/components/HomePage/home.css`

**Base (desktop, `>768px`) — line 23:**
```css
.newsfeed-header {
    position: fixed;
    display: none;           /* HIDDEN on desktop */
    background-color: var(--bg-backdrop);
    backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
    justify-content: space-evenly;
    align-items: center;
    width: 750px;
    height: 90px;
    border-bottom: 0.7px solid var(--border-light);
    z-index: 120;
}
```

**`@media (max-width: 768px)` — line 342:**
```css
.newsfeed-header {
    position: fixed;
    display: flex;           /* SHOWN at tablet */
    background-color: var(--bg-backdrop);
    backdrop-filter: blur(25px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(5px);
    justify-content: space-evenly;
    align-items: center;
    width: 550px;
    height: 90px;
    border-bottom: 0.7px solid var(--border-light);
    z-index: 1;
}
```

**`@media (max-width: 428px)` — line 404:**
```css
.newsfeed-header {
    position: fixed;
    display: flex;
    background-color: var(--bg-backdrop);
